		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I asked about this a couple months ago. <!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=9&amp;t=9912">viewtopic.php?f=9&amp;t=9912</a><!-- l --> <br />Quietust had a few ideas as to what might be breaking (more OAMADDR oddness). There were a few confirmations, too.<br /><br />Regarding alignment, at least for me, it seems to be more often a thermal issue. But &quot;alignment&quot; plus &quot;thermal&quot; would be code for &quot;timing&quot;, since ICs get slower as they get hotter.

		

		</td>
